Name: Avvance APIs
Description:
# Overview

This API follows common REST API standards and practices and most HTTP clients will likely support it. Standard HTTP authentication methods and response status codes are used. We recommend using either a rest client like Postman or cURL, you can retrieve existing resources and begin to explore the API with just a browser.

Parameters.Name: Authorization
Parameters.Description: The Base64 encoded key and secret. Your key and secret key will be provided by Avvance when you start your project.

x-codeSamples.source:
curl --location --request POST  'https://dev-api.usbank.com/poslp/services/partner/enroll-merchant'  \
--header 'Content-Type: application/json' \
--header 'Authorization: Bearer JaV2IAugx8yUG4jGwS9kVmlAWrM4' \
--header 'channel-id: owa' \
--header 'Correlation-ID: 34444' \
--header 'application-id: test' \
--header 'Partner-ID: UAT_Test_BNPL_Partner_success' \
--header 'routingKey: it1' \
--header 'clientdata: { "ChannelID":"owa" }' \
--header 'Session-ID: dededed' \

EndpointGroups.Name: Authentication Request
EndpointGroups.Description:
Avvance REST APIs use OAuth 2.0 access tokens to authenticate requests. In order to set up the OAuth integration and token request, the following steps will be performed:

1. Avvance will send instructions including a key and a secret, securely to you. Your key and secret will need to be Base64 encoded as key:secret 
2. Get a token via the /token endpoint. Send your encoded client credentials in the header. Avvance will return an access token.
3. Send the access token in the header for all other operations.
4. Subsequent tokens are acquired by sending an authentication request to /token endpoint and receiving a new valid token, regardless of the expiration time of the previously received token. There is no refresh token mechanism.

Never share your secret key. Keep it guarded and secure.

EndpointGroups.Name: Initiate Loan
EndpointGroups.Description: This loan initiation API accepts the invoice amount, customer email or phone number to generate and return the unique customer application URL. This unique URL can be used in invoice email, text or used to generate a QR code which customers can use to start the Avvance loan process.

EndpointGroups.Name: Enroll Merchant Request
EndpointGroups.Description: The partner merchant onboarding API facilitates the initiation of the enrollment process by accepting the parameters such as merchantId, firstName, lastName and applicantEmail. Upon submission, it generates and returns a unique URL dedicated to the merchant's application. This exclusive url serves as the gateway for merchants to commence their enrollment journey seamlessly.

EndpointGroups.Name: Void
EndpointGroups.Description: Void API is a POST request that voids a previous Avvance purchase or refund transaction. Only Avvance transactions that are not settled can be voided.

EndpointGroups.Name: Refund
EndpointGroups.Description: Refund API is a POST request that refunds a previous Avvance purchase. Only Avvance transactions that are settled can be refunded. Partial refunds are allowed. Sum of partial refund amount cannot exceed the original Avvance purchase amount.

EndpointGroups.Name: Loan Status
EndpointGroups.Description: Avvance sends webhooks to partners for customer loan status for their invoice.

EndpointGroups.Name: Reporting
EndpointGroups.Description: Reporting API retrieves the transactions associated with the merchants and the partners.

Fields.Name: terminalId
Fields.Description:
The terminal identification number used to uniquely identify the Merchant and their financial institution to Elavon.  
The terminal ID consists of two parts and is assigned by Elavon for each POS device.  
- Digits 1-6 = Bank Number  This six-digit fixed length value is assigned by Elavon.  
- Digits 7-22 = Terminal Number or ID  This variable length value is assigned by Elavon and has a minimum length of 1 and a maximum length of 16.
